2. **Initial Value**: The initial value of interest receivable is typically zero at the start of the period unless there are carryover amounts from previous periods. In the given data, there are no initial interest receivable entries before the first transaction, so the initial value is 0.

3. **End Value**: The end value is the sum of all "Interest Receivables" transactions where the "payment/receipt_status" is "Unpaid". This represents the total interest that has been earned but not yet received by the end of the period.
